<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>QuickBooks Integration Checklist</h1>
        <p>Follow this checklist to set up and integrate with QuickBooks Online (QBO) API.</p>

        <h2>1. App Credentials</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Client ID:</strong> Your app's unique identifier from the Intuit Developer Portal.</li>
            <li><strong>Client Secret:</strong> A secret key for authenticating your app.</li>
            <li><strong>Where to find:</strong> 
                <ul>
                    <li>Log in to the <a href="https://developer.intuit.com/" target="_blank">Intuit Developer Portal</a>.</li>
                    <li>Go to <strong>Dashboard > Your App > Keys & OAuth</strong>.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>2. Redirect URI</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Purpose:</strong> Specifies where QuickBooks redirects users after authorization.</li>
            <li><strong>Example:</strong> <span class="code">https://script.google.com/macros/s/YOUR_DEPLOYMENT_ID/usercallback</span></li>
            <li><strong>Configuration:</strong> Add this to the Redirect URI section in the Intuit Developer Portal.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>3. Scopes</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Purpose:</strong> Define the level of access your app requires.</li>
            <li><strong>Common Scopes:</strong>
                <ul>
                    <li><span class="code">com.intuit.quickbooks.accounting</span>: Access accounting data.</li>
                    <li><span class="code">com.intuit.quickbooks.payroll</span>: Access payroll data.</li>
                    <li><span class="code">openid</span>: Access user profile information.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>4. Realm ID (Company ID)</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Purpose:</strong> Identifies the QuickBooks company you're working with.</li>
            <li><strong>How to get:</strong> 
                <span class="code">https://YOUR_REDIRECT_URI?code=AUTH_CODE&realmId=REALM_ID</span>
                (found in the callback URL after authorization).
            </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>5. Access and Refresh Tokens</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Access Token:</strong> Used for making API calls.</li>
            <li><strong>Refresh Token:</strong> Used to refresh the access token when it expires.</li>
            <li><strong>Retrieve Tokens:</strong> Use the <span class="code">/oauth2/v1/tokens/bearer</span> endpoint.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>6. Base API URLs</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Sandbox Environment:</strong> 
                <span class="code">https://sandbox-quickbooks.api.intuit.com/v3/company/{realmId}</span>
            </li>
            <li><strong>Production Environment:</strong> 
                <span class="code">https://quickbooks.api.intuit.com/v3/company/{realmId}</span>
            </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>7. API Endpoints</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Customers:</strong> <span class="code">/customer</span> (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE)</li>
            <li><strong>Invoices:</strong> <span class="code">/invoice</span> (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE)</li>
            <li><strong>Payroll:</strong> <span class="code">/payroll</span> (if enabled)</li>
            <li><strong>Reports:</strong> <span class="code">/reports/{reportName}</span></li>
            <li>For more details, visit the <a href="https://developer.intuit.com/app/developer/qbo/docs/api/accounting/most-commonly-used" target="_blank">QuickBooks API Documentation</a>.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>8. Sandbox Testing</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Purpose:</strong> Use the sandbox to test API requests without affecting live data.</li>
            <li><strong>Base URL:</strong> 
                <span class="code">https://sandbox-quickbooks.api.intuit.com/v3/company/{realmId}</span>
            </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Checklist Summary</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Configure your app in the Intuit Developer Portal.</li>
            <li>Set up a Redirect URI and select the required scopes.</li>
            <li>Test the OAuth2 flow and retrieve tokens.</li>
            <li>Validate API connectivity using sandbox endpoints.</li>
            <li>Log API requests and responses for debugging.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
